    {
      "id": "adf762076b0e0a4ef36777ebf9eb323352a3ed32",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-07-11 17:44:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI think yes.  Essentially we need to be able to continually re-generate the upstream kernel client code from the Lustre master code, to be able to detect patches that are missing in either direction.  I wouldn't want the \"diff\" of these two trees to be landed on either codebase (instead the individual patches should be cherry-picked between branches), but at least it will serve as a sanity check to ensure the codes stay in sync.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
